parameters: I don't want the player to be able to enter the bedrooms of the
NPCs, so I'm using these white sheets to show that.
Want this to be a 4-5 year old girl playing with her dolls.
Want there to be reference to this family loving to host
events and get togethers for the village when it starts getting
colder outside and the fire pit doesn't feel like a good idea.
Could be a story point/event for if the player helps the village
a ton, the family here will host a small party and there be some
REALLY tasty food. If player isn't pregnant, then she'll eat a ton
*wink wink nudge nudge* ;P
The woman of the house will be here frantically cooking away
preparing for a party that they plan on hosting soon.
By soon, I mean that it'll happen as a reward for helping
the villagers.
She'll mention to the player that they should empty their belly
if they're going to join the party since it's the most food she's
made before.
Not fully sure how to decorage the kid's bedrooms, but this top one
is for the little girl, and the lower one for the older brother.
Door here, Building 1
Door
Wine maker maybe mentions that his/her bedroom is lo long so as to
avoid the fumes making her drunk while she sleeps since they can
already get pretty drunk sometimes just while making the wine.
They have a VERY low tolerence.
Potential questline being finding a plant in the forest that
______ knows boosts alcohol tolerance by quite a lot, but that
______ doesn't want to go into the forest due to the hunter of
the villag ebeing injured by wolves in there.
Next shipment for the kingdom's Capital is here, just waiting
for the caravans to appear. If player explors forest, they come
across a caravan being surrounded by a huge pack of wolves.
Fighting them frees the caravan to come and pick all this up.
The older woman in this house does a lot with textiles,
and is first found working on this set of clothes.
Old man of the house does a lot of painting since he can't help
with much else. Was the previous mayor, so he does help current mayor
with those kinds of decisions occasionally.
